summary: An Ordinance amending Section Three of Ordinance No. 15215, entitled "An Ordinance granting to The Seattle Electric Company, its successors and assigns, a franchise to construct, maintain and operate a street railway upon certain parts of Ewing Street, Wallingford Avenue and other streets, avenues and places in the City of Seattle", which became a law January 14, 1907, and requiring the acceptance by the grantee of this amendatory ordinance.
